OL,7,FMs Ward, who is the first player to
OL,8,Fbenefit from the Rugby and Football
OL,9,FUnion's (RFU) new maternity policy,
OL,10,Fsaid women face "so many pressures"
OL,11,Fwhen they become mothers.
OL,13,FThe new RFU policy gives women full
OL,14,Fpay for 26 weeks of maternity leave.
OL,15,FIt also gives players the option to
OL,16,Fmove into other safe employment within
OL,17,Fthe rugby network, while protecting
OL,18,Ftheir ability to continue playing the
OL,19,Fgame professionally on their return.
